explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the diagnostic capability of a specific neuroretinal rim parameter (BMO-MRW) in detecting open-angle glaucoma using spectral-domain optical coherence tomography (SD-OCT) and confocal scanning laser tomography (CSLT). It does not mention or involve any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models such as supervised learning, unsupervised learning, neural networks, or any other related keywords listed. The study is purely based on medical imaging and clinical assessment methods.
